  "response_text": "# Getting Enough Fiber Daily\n\n## Easy High-Fiber Foods\n\n**Whole grains**\n- Oatmeal, brown rice, whole wheat bread\n- Quinoa, barley\n\n**Fruits & vegetables**\n- Berries, pears, apples (with skin)\n- Broccoli, carrots, sweet potatoes, leafy greens\n\n**Legumes**\n- Beans, lentils, chickpeas\n- Split peas\n\n**Other sources**\n- Nuts and seeds\n- Chia seeds, flaxseeds\n\n## Practical Tips\n\n- **Swap gradually** — increase fiber slowly to avoid digestive discomfort\n- **Drink more water** — fiber works best with adequate hydration\n- **Eat skins** — fruit and vegetable skins contain lots of fiber\n- **Choose whole grains** over refined versions\n- **Snack smart** — nuts, seeds, or fruit instead of processed snacks\n\n## Daily Goals\n\n- Women: 25g per day\n- Men: 38g per day\n\n## Quick Wins\n\n- Add beans to salads or soups\n- Sprinkle seeds on yogurt or cereal\n- Choose whole grain bread\n- Keep fruit handy for snacking\n\n**Note:** If you have digestive issues or are on medications, check with your doctor before making major dietary changes.",
